Package TableStructures

Class TableAttributeValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • Concepts.AttributeValue
      • TableStructures.TableAttributeValue

  • public class TableAttributeValue
extends AttributeValue
    This class allows one to view a particular column of a TableObject as an attribute value. Example:
    Consider a table type MarkList with columns "Participant, Semester, Mark"
    A TableAttributeValue could now specify the list of Participants as a list of attribute values. Given an IndividualConcept "exam44", with attribute "MarkList", one could add a ConceptAttribute "participants" with attribute values generated by the TableAttributeValue.

      • find

        public <T> T find​(Operators operator,
                  DataObject otherValue,
                  AttributeValueList otherConstraints,
                  Context context,
                  java.util.function.Function<DataObject,T> function)
        searches through the attribute values to find the first one satisfying the conditions, and where the function returns not null. The conditions are:
        - if operator != null then 'value operator otherValue' must return true
        - if otherConstraints != null the 'this.constraints implies otherConstraints' must return true.
